{
  "texts": [
    "For a secret s ∈ R k q that is chosen according to χ s, sample a ∈ R k q uniformly, and sample an error e ∈ R q from χ e.",
    "The GLWE distribution computes b:= a • s + e ∈ R q, and outputs (a, b).",
    "Definition 8 (Decision GLWE).",
    "The Decision GLWE problem asks to decide whether samples (a, b) are from the GLWE distribution or are chosen uniformly at random from R k+1 q.",
    "Definition 9 (Search GLWE)."
  ]
}